news.title: Lucknow development body razes six-floor building, reclaims land worth Rs 60 crore
news.para: LDA officials said construction on 2,800 sqm land was going on since 2016 without the approval of its map from LDA, following which an FIR was lodged.

news.title: Pune civic body allocates 1,030 houses via lottery under PMAY scheme
news.para: The said flats will be available in areas like Kharadi, Hadapsar and Wadgaon. Over 20,000 applications have come in. PMC had conducted an online lottery for the same in October 2020.

news.title: Ready reckoner rates will match market pulse: Maharashtra IGR
news.para: Confederation of Real Estate Developers’ Associations of India (Credai) state president Sunil Furde said the last time the RR rates were hiked was in September 2020.

news.title: AUDA refuses to give 40 plots to Ahmedabad civic body
news.para: “Just when the jurisdiction of Bopal-Ghuma was transferred to the AMC, AUDA appealed to the state government to allow them to keep the 40 plots. This was accepted and the plots were never transferred to the AMC,” said a senior AUDA official.

news.title: Property taxpayers make a beeline at suvidha centres in Ludhiana
news.para: On Wednesday till 5pm, officials generated Rs 1.34 crore from property tax: Rs 47.77 lakh were collected online, Rs 76.10 lakh at suvidha centers and Rs 10.38 lakh were received by employees manually from taxpayers.

news.title: Noida Authority stops construction activity in Antriksh Golf View 1
news.para: The crackdown on the alleged illegal construction at Antriksh Golf View 1 comes barely two days after the Noida Authority embarked on a drive to raze as many as 47 illegal shops and 20 unauthorised studio apartments at Gardenia Gateway Society in Sector 75.

news.title: ED attaches Pushpanjali Realms & Infratech's assets worth over Rs 31 crore
news.para: ​The ED initiated a money-laundering investigation on the basis of an FIR lodged at the Rajpur police station in the city in July 2020 against the firm, its directors and others for cheating and duping innocent flat buyers after taking advance payments from them.

news.title: SC dismisses bail plea of ex-CFO of Amrapali Group, directs framing of charges against him
news.para: While noting that charge sheet has been filed in three cases, the bench said, "It appears that in all three complaints which have been filed by the ED the petitioner is the only natural person who is arrayed as accused apart from corporate entities in the third complaint".

news.title: Seven banks to disburse Rs 1,500 crore for completion of Amrapali projects
news.para: ​The state-owned NBCC has undertaken the completion of many residential projects in Noida and Greater Noida under the aegis of Amrapali Stalled Projects and Investment Reconstruction Establishment (ASPIRE) and supervision of the Supreme Court.

news.title: RERA council to discuss structural safety of high-rise buildings on April 12
news.para: There are 30 members in the panel which includes Niti Aayog CEO and secretaries of many ministries. FPCE president as well as presidents of realtors' body CREDAI and Naredco are also members of the council.

news.title: NCLT orders insolvency proceedings against Santasha Real Estate
news.para: Vani Advertising, in its petition filed through its counsel Namit Saxena, had submitted that an amount of Rs 40.77 lakh was due on the real estate firm in return for the advertising services provided by it.

news.title: Godrej Properties to develop nine acre project in Pimpri-Chinchwad
news.para: The project has a developable potential of approximately 1.7 million sq ft of saleable area with an estimated revenue potential of approximately Rs 1,400 crore.

news.title: WeWork names CEO Sandeep Mathrani as chairman
news.para: Mathrani, a real estate industry veteran, was named WeWork's chief executive in 2020 and given the task of executing a turnaround after an IPO attempt and investor concerns over corporate governance standards.

news.title: Sunac China seeks investor approval to extend payment for $629 million bond by 18 months
news.para: Hong Kong-listed shares of Sunac, China's No. 3 property developer by sales, jumped more than 21% on Wednesday afternoon, versus a 7% rise in the Hang Seng Mainland Properties Index .

news.title: China Evergrande Group to sell Crystal City Project for $575 million
news.para: The firm is selling the land-use and building ownership rights for the project, which is under construction, to Zhejiang Zhejian Real Estate Group and Zhejiang Construction Engineering Group, Evergrande said in a filing.
